Trading boils down to going with the trend in your timeframe with discipline while managing risk.   For profitable trading it all boils down to big wins & small losses or a high winning percent with small losses.   All else is commentary on how to do this.
Blockchain is the financial internet of the future.
A profitable trading system just needs big wins & small losses. Winning percentage is not the most important factor.
The trick is not becoming a trader. The trick is staying a trader.

If you‚Äôre going to trade, decide on three things at the start: the entry signal, the position size, and the quitting time when it‚Äôs time to exit with a small loss, a small profit, or a big profit.

The financial market is a strict teacher. It‚Äôll keep pushing you in the direction of the mistakes you‚Äôre making until you learn lessons. Sometimes, it feels like the price action is working against you & there is a conspiracy. The market is not an adversary it is an educator.

Advice to my younger self:  Read more books before starting to trade.  Memorizing facts is not the same as learning to trade.  Ask experienced traders better questions.  Work on creating my own trading system.   Put in more effort to speed up the learning curve.  Be realistic.
Why is trading so hard? Human nature has trouble accepting losses quickly and always wants to break dicipline and make a trade happen to create a big win.

What traders can't control: Trends Whip saws Volatility Size of wins Breaking news Politics Central bank actions Earnings reports
What traders can control: Entries Exits Stop losses Trailing stops Profit targets Position size Consistency Watchlist Number of positions
In trading you can't control what the market will do you can only control what you will do.
Trading errors caused by laziness:  Not developing your own entry signals. Not creating a trading plan. Not backtesting a trading system.
Trading errors caused by ego:  Believing you can predict the future. Trading all in on one trade. Not being able exit a losing trade.
Trading errors caused by greed:  Expose an account to too much risk.  Trade too big.  Don't have plans to take profits off the table.
Trading errors caused by fear:  Don't take an entry signal. Don't trade with enough size. Don't let a winner run.
